50|$|Russula sardonia, {{commonly}} known as the <b>primrose</b> <b>brittlegill,</b> is a mushroom of the Russula genus, which are {{commonly known}} as brittlegills. The fruiting body, or mushroom, is a reddish-purple, the colour of blackberry juice, and is found in coniferous woodland in summer and autumn. It is inedible, and like many inedible members of the genus, has a hot, peppery taste.|$|E

